properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 9 at 9:27AM CST until February 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Accumulating Sleet and Snow Today...

.A fast moving storm system will bring a round of snow to the
area. Through very early afternoon, moderate to briefly heavy
snow is possible with snowfall rates approaching 1 inch per hour.
The main impacts from the snow will be slippery roads and
significantly reduced visibilities.

* WHAT...Mixed Precipitation is expected. Total snow
accumulations of 1 to 2 inches. Winds gusting up to 30 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of east central Iowa and north central and
northwest Illinois.

* WHEN...From 9 AM this morning to 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and significantly
reduced visibilities.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow rates are expected to
fall through Noon. Up to 1 inch per hour is possible along with
heavy sleet showers.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions.
In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
